#!hexa strict
// hexa-meta/verify/run_all.hexa — meta-layer verification orchestrator.
//
// hexa-meta's closure pattern is multi-tier:
//   (1) executable verify_*.hexa scripts under predictions/ + constants/
//   (2) Lean 4 formal stubs under formal/lean4/ (sorry-marked per stub policy)
//   (3) document layers (proofs/ + papers/) — meta-theorems with citations
//   (4) tools/ — domain-agnostic engines (smoke-runs only)
//
// This orchestrator covers tier (1): the executable verify scripts. Tier (2)
// is verified by `lake build` (external Lean toolchain). Tiers (3)–(4) are
// document/engine layers and are NOT measurement-reducible — see
// LIMIT_BREAKTHROUGH.md §3.6 (Gödel HARD_WALL) for honest framing.
//
// Run:
//     hexa run verify/run_all.hexa     # exit 0 = all subscripts run rc=0
//
// Honest semantics:
//   - rc=0 from each subscript means the script *executed* without runtime
//     error. Internal PASS/FAIL counts are reported by each script.
//   - Memory-cap exits (rc=77 from hexa-runtime mem cap) are NOT verification
//     failures; they are environmental. This orchestrator does not run the
//     heavy DSE/miner tools — see tools/* individually.
//   - STUB scripts (verify_bt414_430.hexa, etc.) are counted as STUB, not PASS.

